lass=\"articleLead\">\r\n<h2>Paradoxically, Andhra Pradesh though bogged down by a plethora of problems has done exceedingly well in the number of property and land registrations, way ahead of the real estate market in Telangana.</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"body\">More than a year after the bifurcation, the realty market in both Andhra Pradesh and Telangana has significantly improved and cash registers of the Stamps and Registration Departments have started ringing in both the States.</p>\r\n<p class=\"body\">If for Telangana where the real estate market remained stagnant due to years of political uncertainty following agitation for a separate State, things are looking up after the formation of Telangana and Brand Hyderabad continues to be a draw.</p>\r\n<p class=\"body\">Paradoxically, Andhra Pradesh though bogged down by a plethora of problems – financial crunch, no capital of its own, lack of infrastructure and industries to match with common capital of Hyderabad -- an owner’s pride and neighbour’s envy-- has done exceedingly well in the number of property and land registrations, way ahead of the real estate market in Telangana.</p>\r\n<p class=\"body\">It posted a revenue of Rs. 1,239.29 crore, exceeding the target of Rs.1,172 crore up to July 2015, as against Rs.1,008.45 crore garnered by Telangana from the Registration Department though in geographical as well as urban towns wise Andhra is way ahead.</p>\r\n<p class=\"body\">Andhra Pradesh though overall suffered a revenue shortfall of about Rs. 3,000 crore, the revenue from the Stamps and Registration department in the first quarter of 2015-16 saw a substantial jump registering over 105 per cent achievement than the target compared to that of last year.</p>\r\n<p class=\"body\">However in Telangana, barring Ranga Reddy (Rs. 480 crore) and Hyderabad (Rs. 215 crore) districts which accounted for 21 per cent and 48 per cent respectively and together for 70 per cent total registration revenue of the State, remaining eight districts could only post nominal revenue.</p>\r\n<p class=\"body\"><img class=\"alignnone\" src=\"http://www.thehindu.com/multimedia/dynamic/02525/VJ25REGISTRATION_e_2525789g.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"630\" height=\"301\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"body\"><b>Vizag top grosser</b></p>\r\n<p class=\"body\">Andhra Pradesh, on the other hand, has all its districts doing well in earning revenue from registrations. Visakhapatnam district, touted to become the next IT hub, turned out to be the top grosser with Rs. 204 crore (17 per cent of total State registration revenue) , Krishna district Rs. 171.6 crore (14 per cent) and Guntur, the district boasting the new capital region, at third place with Rs. 161 crore, East Godavari- Rs. 150 crore West Godvari – Rs.104 crore.</p>\r\n<p class=\"body\">Though the State banked heavily on Krishna and Guntur which are close to the capital region of Amaravati and set ambitious targets for them, they could not surpass the target but the surprise came from the North Andhra districts of Srikakulam and Vizianagaram -- where a Greenfield international airport is proposed near Bhogapuram -- as they posted revenue much beyond the expectations.</p>\r\n<p class=\"body\">The other districts -- Nellore, Prakasam and four Rayalaseema districts -- Chittoor, Kadapa, Anantapur and Kurnool -- either achieved the target or exceeded it till July.</p>\r\n<p class=\"body\">Nothing short of frenzy is being witnessed in Andhra based on strong sentiment for growth and development and people are keen to invest in the highly speculative market across the State. With the State government earmarking different industrial and infrastructure projects for different districts with anticipated industrial concessions and special package from the Centre, the scenario is reminiscent of the boom phase which Hyderabad went through during 2005 to 2007 till global recession put a halt to it, say official sources in both the States.</p>\r\n<p class=\"body\">Ironically while Hyderabad is a boon for Telangana, it is also an inhibiting factor for growth of the other districts. With so much land available in Hyderabad and neighbourhood, investors do not look beyond vicinity of Hyderabad which has futuristic amenities to set up their units.</p>','Andhra Pradesh surges ahead of Telangana in the real estate race','','publish','open','open','','test-1','','','2015-12-22 07:44:24','2015-12-22 07:44:24','',0,'http://caltechsoft.com/rankprop/?p=280',0,'post','',0),(281,1,'2015-12-19 07:24:57','2015-12-19 07:24:57','In Andhra Pradesh we are the best interior designers, we have creative and dynamic team of Designers and experienced Architects Amaze Properties is a real estate company located in Kurnool, Andhra Pradesh.In Andhra Pradesh we are the best interior designers, we have creative and dynamic team of Designers and experienced Architects Amaze Properties is a real estate company located in Kurnool, Andhra Pradesh.','Test 1','','inherit','closed','closed','','280-revision-v1','','','2015-12-19 07:24:57','2015-12-19 07:24:57','',280,'http://caltechsoft.com/rankprop/280-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(282,1,'2015-12-19 07:25:13','2015-12-19 07:25:13','Meanwhile the land broker is busy haggling with Srinivas who works in Dallas, USA about a couple of hundred rupees per square yard which he deems difficult to concede, especially given the fact that the piece of land is much closer to the highway. “They are selling like hotcake everywhere, everything closer to the heart of the city is already taken! Especially given the fact that you have to be politically connected to get some land around Vijayawada the new capital” says Babloo.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://image.indiaopines.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/NRI-REAL-ESTATE.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"599\" height=\"398\" />\r\n\r\nA number of sources have revealed the same story that everything in Vijayawada needs a certain level of influence and most of it has already been settled by the dominant ones (politically) and the well connected owing to various other reasons. Vijayawada has been declared as the grand capital of Andhra Pradesh by Mr. Chandrababu Naidu the Chief Minister of the state who plans to build it on the lines of Singapore.\r\n\r\nIn Vishakhapatnam the story seems to be slightly different with land still being available although at highly inflated prices that have quadrupled since the erstwhile state of Andhra Pradesh split into two. A number of companies have since then sprung up in the residual state of Andhra Pradesh (which goes by its parent name) that have been offering land at highly exorbitant rates.\r\n\r\nSome of these companies like Nivas properties are using novel methods like email marketing to target the NRI’s spread in the US and other countries, especially the large Telugu community which is spread across the US. Some of them go with a catch “Sea view from First floor (if constructed)!” Others measure the distance from the beach. 2000, 3000, 5000… You name it. Unfortunately to many of the fisherman communities living around, the distance is several hundreds of thousands of feet from this prized land, in spite of them living so close to it.\r\n\r\nThere is an intense competition playing out between Chandrababu Naidu the Chief Minister of Andhra Pradesh and K Chandrasekhar Rao the Chief Minister of Telangana that has excited the NRI’s living in the US from both Andhra Pradesh and Telangana. While K Chandrasekhar Rao popularly known as KCR plans to develop Hyderabad further on the lines of Istanbul in Turkey and Shanghai in China, Naidu is readying plans to transform Vijaywada into Singapore complete with a newly built skyline.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','NRI’s creating a Real Estate Bubble in the New State of Andhra Pradesh?','','publish','open','open','','test-2','','','2015-12-22 07:59:52','2015-12-22 07:59:52','',0,'http://caltechsoft.com/rankprop/?p=282',0,'post','',0),(283,1,'2015-12-19 07:25:13','2015-12-19 07:25:13','In Andhra Pradesh we are the best interior designers, we have creative and dynamic team of Designers and experienced Architects Amaze Properties is a real estate company located in Kurnool, Andhra Pradesh.In Andhra Pradesh we are the best interior designers, we have creative and dynamic team of Designers and experienced Architects Amaze Properties is a real estate company located in Kurnool, Andhra Pradesh.','Test 2','','inherit','closed','closed','','282-revision-v1','','','2015-12-19 07:25:13','2015-12-19 07:25:13','',282,'http://caltechsoft.com/rankprop/282-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(284,1,'2015-12-19 07:25:34','2015-12-19 07:25:34','<i>Since the search to find the new capital for Seemandhra is on, Guntur has also emerged as a strong contender. It seems that Guntur’s future is bright once the two states split.</i>\r\n\r\nSituated on the banks of Krishna river delta, Guntur is a centre for business and commerce of various industries, such as textile and agriculture industries. In recent years, the city has gained prominence due to its thriving spice industry. The long coastal line and highways in the city allows the traders to export their products to different parts of the country and the world.\r\n\r\nThe city is experiencing a lot of development in its infrastructure and transportation in the recent years. So, what lies ahead for the city of spices?\r\n\r\n<b>Real estate scenario </b>\r\n\r\nAccording to Magicbricks data, the current rates of apartment in the city are between Rs 3000- Rs 3500 per sq ft. A 2BHK apartment in Guntur having a 1000-1200 sq ft area costs between Rs 40-45 lakh. However, the rates in the outer areas of Guntur are comparatively less. However, owning a property in the outskirts of Guntur is quite cheaper as the starting price of a 2BHK apartment (1000-1200 sq ft area) in Gorantla is just Rs 20 lakh.\r\n\r\nWith a lot of private companies coming up in the city and setting up their offices here, market experts in the city expect a substantial amount of growth in the next five years. “There is availability of state land to set up government offices. Infrastructure in the city is good and we have excellent connectivity with other parts of Seemandhra,” says Siva, managing director of Sri Bala Krishna Construction, a local developer.\r\n\r\n“We are already seeing a positive growth in the real estate industry of the city. Real estate prices have risen up to 20 per cent in the last three months,” he adds.\r\n\r\nPeople who are investing in the properties are NRIs, people from other parts of state and a few local people. “Most of them are end users but now the investors too have started investing in the properties here,” says Siva.\r\n\r\nAn IT Park and a textile hub are already being set up near Guntur and thus are likely to draw in hundreds of jobs in the city. Moreover, government has proposed to build two new plans – Knowledge Park and Biotechnology Park.\r\n\r\n“Once the city starts providing more employment opportunities, people will migrate here from different parts of Seemandhra, all these people are definitely going to invest in the properties here,” says Naidu Rao, marketing head of SVR Developers.\r\n\r\n<b>Infrastructure </b>\r\n\r\nWhen it comes to transportation, Guntur is well-connected to all the major cities such as Chennai, Kolkata, Hyderabad, Vijaywada, Tenali, Kurnool, Bellary and all other parts of Seemandhra. Government has also laid plans to improve the two main railway stations of the city – one in Arundelpet and the other in Railpet. The international airport that is being planned in Vijaywada is just 45 km away from the city.\r\n\r\n“Good connectivity, availability of schools, colleges, hospitals, availability of water, industries, coast; Guntur has all major ingredients that a city needs to grow. The future of the city seems promising,” adds Rao.\r\n\r\nKrishna River provides ample water to the citizens of the city and all the industries that are situated in the area. Some parts of Seemandhra, especially the areas under Rayalaseema, have a huge water shortage. Thus, availability of water in Guntur is attracting more industries to the city.','Guntur’s future looks promising post Telangana','','publish','open','open','','test-3','','','2015-12-22 08:01:38','2015-12-22 08:01:38','',0,'http://caltechsoft.com/rankprop/?p=284',0,'post','',0),(285,1,'2015-12-19 07:25:34','2015-12-19 07:25:34','In Andhra Pradesh we are the best interior designers, we have creative and dynamic team of Designers and experienced Architects Amaze Properties is a real estate company located in Kurnool, Andhra Pradesh. In Andhra Pradesh we are the best interior designers, we have creative and dynamic team of Designers and experienced Architects Amaze Properties is a real estate company located in Kurnool, Andhra Pradesh.','Test 3','','inherit','closed','closed','','284-revision-v1','','','2015-12-19 07:25:34','2015-12-19 07:25:34','',284,'http://caltechsoft.com/rankprop/284-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(286,1,'2015-12-19 07:26:11','2015-12-19 07:26:11','','Blog','','publish','closed','closed','','blog','','','2016-01-02 09:58:02','2016-01-02 09:58:02','',0,'http://caltechsoft.com/rankprop/?p=286',16,'nav_menu_item','',0),(287,1,'2015-12-19 07:26:33','2015-12-19 07:26:33','','Blog Page','','publish','closed','closed','','blog-page','','','2015-12-19 07:26:33','2015-12-19 07:26:33','',0,'http://caltechsoft.com/rankprop/?post_type=sidebar&#038;p=287',0,'sidebar','',0),(290,1,'2015-12-19 10:00:02','2015-12-19 10:00:02','[vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=\"Registration\" font_container=\"tag:h2|text_align:left\" google_fonts=\"font_family:Abril%20Fatface%3Aregular|font_style:400%20regular%3A400%3Anormal\"][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\nI am text block. Click edit button to change this text. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Ut elit tellus, luctus nec ullamcorper mattis, pulvinar dapibus leo.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Sig